agentInventory.name: agentInventory
agentInventory.description: This MIB defines the objects used to configure and report information and status of units, slots and supported cards.

AgentInventoryUnitPreference.name: AgentInventoryUnitPreference
AgentInventoryUnitPreference.description: Indicates the preference the unit has for being the management unit in the stack. If the value is 0, it indicates the unit is disabled for management.

AgentInventoryUnitType.name: AgentInventoryUnitType
AgentInventoryUnitType.description: The Unit Type value for a given unit, displayed in hexadecimal.

AgentInventoryCardType.name: AgentInventoryCardType
AgentInventoryCardType.description: The Card Type value for a given card, displayed in hexadecimal.

agentInventoryStackReplicateSTK.name: agentInventoryStackReplicateSTK
agentInventoryStackReplicateSTK.description: Initiates STK copy from management unit to all other management capable units in the stack.

agentInventoryStackMaxUnitNumber.name: agentInventoryStackMaxUnitNumber
agentInventoryStackMaxUnitNumber.description: Indicates the maximum allowed Unit Number configurable on the stack.

agentInventoryStackReplicateSTKStatus.name: agentInventoryStackReplicateSTKStatus
agentInventoryStackReplicateSTKStatus.description: Indicates the current status of an STK copy from management unit to all other management capable units inthe stack.

agentInventorySupportedUnitIndex.name: agentInventorySupportedUnitIndex
agentInventorySupportedUnitIndex.description: The unit identifier associated with the supported unit.

agentInventorySupportedUnitModelIdentifi.name: agentInventorySupportedUnitModelIdentifier
agentInventorySupportedUnitModelIdentifi.description: The model identifier for the supported unit.

agentInventorySupportedUnitDescription.name: agentInventorySupportedUnitDescription
agentInventorySupportedUnitDescription.description: The description of the supported unit.

agentInventoryUnitTable.name: agentInventoryUnitTable
agentInventoryUnitTable.description: A table of Per-Unit configuration objects.

agentInventoryUnitEntry.name: agentInventoryUnitEntry
agentInventoryUnitEntry.description: Each Instance corresponds with a different unit managed by this agent.

agentInventoryUnitNumber.name: agentInventoryUnitNumber
agentInventoryUnitNumber.description: The unit number associated with this unit.

agentInventoryUnitAssignNumber.name: agentInventoryUnitAssignNumber
agentInventoryUnitAssignNumber.description: Allows setting the unit number associated with this unit. This number must be less than the value returned by agentInventoryStackMaxUnitNumber. Setting this object to a non-zero value will initate changing the unit number.

agentInventoryUnitType.name: agentInventoryUnitType
agentInventoryUnitType.description: The Unit Type identifier for this unit.

agentInventoryUnitSupportedUnitIndex.name: agentInventoryUnitSupportedUnitIndex
agentInventoryUnitSupportedUnitIndex.description: The index of the unit type in agentInventorySupportedUnitTable which this unit is associated with.

agentInventoryUnitMgmtAdmin.name: agentInventoryUnitMgmtAdmin
agentInventoryUnitMgmtAdmin.description: Indicates whether the unit is a Management Unit, a Stack Unit, or has been configured to be a Management Unit. Setting this object to mgmtUnit(1) initiates transfer of the management functionality to the specified stack unit. Object values stackUnit(2) and mgmtUnassigned(3) cannot be set.

agentInventoryUnitHWMgmtPref.name: agentInventoryUnitHWMgmtPref
agentInventoryUnitHWMgmtPref.description: Indicates the default preference assigned to the unit.

agentInventoryUnitHWMgmtPrefValue.name: agentInventoryUnitHWMgmtPrefValue
agentInventoryUnitHWMgmtPrefValue.description: Indicates the default preference value assigned to the unit. The preference value indicates how likely this unit is to be chosen as the management unit. A value of 0 indicates a disabled or unassigned preference.

agentInventoryUnitAdminMgmtPref.name: agentInventoryUnitAdminMgmtPref
agentInventoryUnitAdminMgmtPref.description: Indicates the configured preference assigned to the unit. This object can not be set to assigned(3). Setting this object to disabled(1), or unassigned(2) will set agentInventoryUnitHWMgmtPrefValue to 0.

agentInventoryUnitAdminMgmtPrefValue.name: agentInventoryUnitAdminMgmtPrefValue
agentInventoryUnitAdminMgmtPrefValue.description: Indicates the configured preference value assigned to the unit. The preference value indicates how likely this unit is to be chosen as the management unit. A value of 0 indicates a disabled or unassigned preference. Setting this object to 0 will also set agentInventoryUnitHWMgmtPref to unassigned(2). Setting this object to a non-zero value will set agentInventoryUnitHWMgmtPref to assigned(3). This value overrides the value of agentInventoryUnitHWMgmtPref if assigned.

agentInventoryUnitStatus.name: agentInventoryUnitStatus
agentInventoryUnitStatus.description: The unit status of this unit.

agentInventoryUnitDetectedCodeVer.name: agentInventoryUnitDetectedCodeVer
agentInventoryUnitDetectedCodeVer.description: The version of code running on this unit. If the unit is not detected then the code version is an empty string.

agentInventoryUnitDetectedCodeInFlashVer.name: agentInventoryUnitDetectedCodeInFlashVer
agentInventoryUnitDetectedCodeInFlashVer.description: The version of code that is currently stored in FLASH memory on the unit. This code will execute after the unit is reset. If the unit is not detected then this object will return an empty string.

agentInventoryUnitUpTime.name: agentInventoryUnitUpTime
agentInventoryUnitUpTime.description: The system up time of the unit.

agentInventoryUnitReplicateSTK.name: agentInventoryUnitReplicateSTK
agentInventoryUnitReplicateSTK.description: Initiates STK copy from management unit to this unit if it is management capable.

agentInventoryUnitReload.name: agentInventoryUnitReload
agentInventoryUnitReload.description: Reload a specific unit in the stack.

agentInventoryUnitRowStatus.name: agentInventoryUnitRowStatus
agentInventoryUnitRowStatus.description: The status of this unit instance. Creation of new instances requires the object agentInventoryUnitSupportedUnitIndex to be set at the same time to indicate the type of of unit to pre-configure. active(1) - This instance is active. createAndGo(4) - Creates a new instance. destroy(6) - Removes this instance.

agentInventoryUnitSerialNumber.name: agentInventoryUnitSerialNumber
agentInventoryUnitSerialNumber.description: The Serial Number of the unit.

agentInventorySlotNumber.name: agentInventorySlotNumber
agentInventorySlotNumber.description: An incrimental index of the slot in this unit.

agentInventorySlotStatus.name: agentInventorySlotStatus
agentInventorySlotStatus.description: Indicates the current status of the slot.

agentInventorySlotPowerMode.name: agentInventorySlotPowerMode
agentInventorySlotPowerMode.description: Indicates whether a card in this slot will be powered on.

agentInventorySlotAdminMode.name: agentInventorySlotAdminMode
agentInventorySlotAdminMode.description: Indicates whether this card is administratively enabled or disabled.

agentInventorySlotInsertedCardType.name: agentInventorySlotInsertedCardType
agentInventorySlotInsertedCardType.description: Indicates the inserted card type. Will return 0 if the slot is not full.

agentInventorySlotConfiguredCardType.name: agentInventorySlotConfiguredCardType
agentInventorySlotConfiguredCardType.description: Indicates the configured card type. This object may be set with a corresponding value of agentInventoryCardType if this slot supports removable cards.

agentInventorySlotCapabilities.name: agentInventorySlotCapabilities
agentInventorySlotCapabilities.description: Indicates the different capabilities this slot has. pluggable(0) - This slot can contain pluggable cards. power-down(1) - Power to this slot can be controlled through the object agentInventorySlotPowerMode

agentInventoryCardTypeTable.name: agentInventoryCardTypeTable
agentInventoryCardTypeTable.description: Contains information for all supported Card Types in the system.

agentInventoryCardTypeEntry.name: agentInventoryCardTypeEntry
agentInventoryCardTypeEntry.description: Contains information related to a specific Card Type.

agentInventoryCardIndex.name: agentInventoryCardIndex
agentInventoryCardIndex.description: An arbitrary index used to identify cards in the table.

agentInventoryCardType.name: agentInventoryCardType
agentInventoryCardType.description: The Card Type associated with this instance.

agentInventoryCardModelIdentifier.name: agentInventoryCardModelIdentifier
agentInventoryCardModelIdentifier.description: The model identifier for the supported Card Type.

agentInventoryCardDescription.name: agentInventoryCardDescription
agentInventoryCardDescription.description: The card description for the supported Card Type.

agentInventoryComponentTable.name: agentInventoryComponentTable
agentInventoryComponentTable.description: Contains information for all supported Components in the system.

agentInventoryComponentEntry.name: agentInventoryComponentEntry
agentInventoryComponentEntry.description: Contains information related to a specific Components.

agentInventoryComponentIndex.name: agentInventoryComponentIndex
agentInventoryComponentIndex.description: An arbitrary index used to reference components in the table.

agentInventoryComponentMnemonic.name: agentInventoryComponentMnemonic
agentInventoryComponentMnemonic.description: The abreviated name of this component.

agentInventoryComponentName.name: agentInventoryComponentName
agentInventoryComponentName.description: The name of the component for this instance.

agentInventoryStackPortIpTelephonyQOSSup.name: agentInventoryStackPortIpTelephonyQOSSupport
agentInventoryStackPortIpTelephonyQOSSup.description: Controls whether the Stack Ports give higher priority to IP Telephony traffic.

agentInventoryStackPortTable.name: agentInventoryStackPortTable
agentInventoryStackPortTable.description: Contains information for all Stack Ports present in the system.

agentInventoryStackPortEntry.name: agentInventoryStackPortEntry
agentInventoryStackPortEntry.description: Contains information related to a specific Stack Port.

agentInventoryStackPortIndex.name: agentInventoryStackPortIndex
agentInventoryStackPortIndex.description: An arbitrary index used to reference Stack Ports in the table.

agentInventoryStackPortUnit.name: agentInventoryStackPortUnit
agentInventoryStackPortUnit.description: The Unit Index this Stack Port is physically located on.

agentInventoryStackPortTag.name: agentInventoryStackPortTag
agentInventoryStackPortTag.description: The name of the Stack Port for this instance.

agentInventoryStackPortConfiguredStackMo.name: agentInventoryStackPortConfiguredStackMode
agentInventoryStackPortConfiguredStackMo.description: Configured mode of the Stack Port. Changes to this value happen only after a reset of the switch.

agentInventoryStackPortRunningStackMode.name: agentInventoryStackPortRunningStackMode
agentInventoryStackPortRunningStackMode.description: Currently operational mode of the Stack Port.

agentInventoryStackPortLinkStatus.name: agentInventoryStackPortLinkStatus
agentInventoryStackPortLinkStatus.description: Link status of the Stack Port. Ports which are in ethernet mode will return a status of down(2).

agentInventoryStackPortLinkSpeed.name: agentInventoryStackPortLinkSpeed
agentInventoryStackPortLinkSpeed.description: Speed of the Stack Port measured in Gb/s. Ports which are in ethernet mode will return a speed of 0.

agentInventoryStackPortDataRate.name: agentInventoryStackPortDataRate
agentInventoryStackPortDataRate.description: Approximate data rate on the stacking port. Measured in Gb/s. Ports which are in ethernet mode will return 0.

agentInventoryStackPortErrorRate.name: agentInventoryStackPortErrorRate
agentInventoryStackPortErrorRate.description: Approximate error rate on the stack port. Measured in Errors per Second. Ports which are in ethernet mode will return 0.

agentInventoryStackPortTotalErrors.name: agentInventoryStackPortTotalErrors
agentInventoryStackPortTotalErrors.description: Number of errors since boot. The counter may wrap. Ports which are in ethernet mode will return 0.

agentInventoryCardMismatch.name: agentInventoryCardMismatch
agentInventoryCardMismatch.description: Sent when a card is inserted which is a different type than what the slot was configured for.

agentInventoryCardUnsupported.name: agentInventoryCardUnsupported
agentInventoryCardUnsupported.description: Sent when a card is inserted which is of a type that is not supported by the slot.

agentInventoryStackPortLinkUp.name: agentInventoryStackPortLinkUp
agentInventoryStackPortLinkUp.description: Sent when a Stack Port is connected to annother Stack Member.

agentInventoryStackPortLinkDown.name: agentInventoryStackPortLinkDown
agentInventoryStackPortLinkDown.description: Sent when a Stack Port is disconnected from annother Stack Member.

agentInventoryCompliance.name: agentInventoryCompliance
agentInventoryCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement version 1 of the agentInventory MIB.

agentInventorySupportedUnitComplianceGro.name: agentInventorySupportedUnitComplianceGroup
agentInventorySupportedUnitComplianceGro.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent multiple units in the stack.

agentInventoryUnitComplienceComplianceGr.name: agentInventoryUnitComplienceComplianceGroup
agentInventoryUnitComplienceComplianceGr.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent multiple units in the stack.

agentInventorySlotComplianceGroup.name: agentInventorySlotComplianceGroup
agentInventorySlotComplianceGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent slots in the each unit managed by this agent.

agentInventoryCardComplianceGroup.name: agentInventoryCardComplianceGroup
agentInventoryCardComplianceGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent the card types this system can manage.

agentInventoryNotificationsComplianceGro.name: agentInventoryNotificationsComplianceGroup
agentInventoryNotificationsComplianceGro.description: The collection of notifications used to indicate problems associated with the insertion of cards.
